careful about formatting; the final output should be a single valid JSON without any comments. Let's focus on getting that right!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"doxia-site-renderer 2.0.0 exposes Maven skin APIs through a provided Maven Artifact type and no longer brings APT parser support transitively; the existing scaffold exercises APT/site rendering paths.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The 2.0.0 public API uses org.apache.maven.artifact.Artifact in SiteRenderingContext/createContextForSkin/copyResources, but doxia-site-renderer declares maven-artifact as provided, so tests that cover skin/resource handling cannot compile without adding it.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The existing tests use APT rendering context, while Doxia 2.0.0 parser modules are discovered from classpath component descriptors and doxia-module-apt is test-scope in the upstream renderer POM, not transitively available from doxia-site-renderer.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For meaningful renderer coverage, instantiate DefaultSiteRenderer through the Plexus/Sisu component container or otherwise inject its Doxia, ParserModuleManager, VelocityComponent, and PlexusContainer collaborators; direct construction leaves those fields null. No Docker image, environment variable, or system property appears required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The compile failure excerpt is primarily an API migration from 1.9.1 to 2.0.0; tests still need to replace removed classes/methods such as RenderingContext, SkinResourceLoader, enableLogging, and setUsingDefaultTemplate.\",\n    \"If generated tests avoid APT inputs and skin/resource APIs entirely, these dependencies may not be strictly necessary, but that would provide weaker coverage of normal Maven site-renderer usage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01a3d3cde99b45b6016a3f8c3630c0819786683e54614b5428\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1026, "output": 1473, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36803, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782549538992, "responseId": "resp_01a3d3cde99b45b6016a3f8c241e908197a19f723ebec4bed8"}}
